      "writtenOn": "2016-08-04T22:06:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m afraid I really didn\u0027t understand the explanation in the spec comment above this very well.  I don\u0027t understand the \"return type int vs. return type void\" stuff.  I mean -- it calls the non-async version, throwing away it\u0027s return value, so it\u0027s going to behave exactly like it, no?\n\nWith the commented-out code above, it feels like you\u0027re preparing for some future extension of the more-concurrent async wait techniques to this flush operation, but that this CL doesn\u0027t go that far.  If that\u0027s what you\u0027re trying to explain, it didn\u0027t come through to me.\n\n---------------------\n\nI read previous comments a little more, and realized that you\u0027re talking about code generated by emugen, from a specification elsewhere of the signature of this call.  I think if you spell that out a bit more, this will make more sense.  Thanks.",
