      "writtenOn": "2016-08-04T22:06:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why the non-standard naming convention?  Because it\u0027s a pseudo-getter?  Maybe the name could say that it also prints it -- the single call to it below reads weirdly because it doesn\u0027t use the out parameter, and the name doesn\u0027t hint that the call has useful-for-debugging side effects.",
