      "writtenOn": "2016-08-04T22:06:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Any chance I could convince you to start using reinterpret_cast for this kind of conversion?\n\nAlso, in this particular case, it seems to me that the cast to uintptr_t (which, BTW, could be a static_cast\u003cuintptr_t\u003e(...)), is unnecessary.  In a previous case, you cited error messages if the intermediate cast were deleted, I believe because the int was 32 bit.  It seems like we\u0027re already assuming 64-bit pointers here, by using uint64_t in the API for thread_ptr.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 617,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 617,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "fc7b89a1c31468cffb7a8642a16888cd68b7c2d7",
